  "description": "The messaging primitives and decisions behind Connect chat on Swarm: PSS for 1-to-1, GSOC for notifications, ACT-protected feed for history.",
  "orientation": "Chat in Connect-on-Swarm is built by matching latency to purpose: PSS trojan chunks deliver 1-to-1 encrypted messages, GSOC gives many-to-one sub-second notifications, and an ACT-protected feed persists history past PSS stamp TTLs. This MOC collects the primitives (PSS, GSOC), the operational constraints (full Bee nodes, sorted-topic derivation), the integration points (share bundles, chat code layout), and the decisions (typing indicators cut, PSS+GSOC combination). It is the reference surface for anyone extending the chat runtime.",
